network_overview: The capture contains sparse 4G/LTE control-plane signaling: SCTP with S1-AP/X2-AP procedures (Proc-11/Proc-13/Proc-23) and multiple Diameter command exchanges (Cmd-318/Cmd-316/Cmd-324) that show Result-Code 2001 (DIAMETER_SUCCESS). A small amount of GTP-C over UDP/2123 and DNS over UDP are present, but there is no observable voice/IMS or media-plane data in the provided evidence.

pattern_matches.explanation: Multiple Diameter Answers explicitly carry Result-Code 2001 labeled as DIAMETER_SUCCESS in the provided deep transactions, demonstrating successful completion for those observed Diameter command exchanges.

observations.finding: Observed Diameter transactions show explicit success (2001) for Cmd-318/Cmd-316/Cmd-324, but the summary counters indicate 'Diameter Sessions: 0' and procedure success_rate 0.0, suggesting metrics aggregation/classification inconsistency rather than protocol failure evidence.

root_causes.issue: Inconclusive: no packet-level failure/reject evidence provided for S1-AP or GTP-C
root_causes.description: The dataset shows S1-AP procedures (Proc-11/Proc-13/Proc-23) with no included cause values, and Diameter exchanges that explicitly succeed (Result-Code 2001). GTP-C is present only as a sparse UDP/2123 flow with no shown message types or cause IEs. Therefore, no concrete reject/error/timeout root cause can be proven from the provided packet-level evidence.
root_causes.impact: Prevents determination of whether any LTE control-plane procedure failed (and why), and prevents correlating S1-AP activity with any GTP-C session lifecycle outcome from this capture.
root_causes.confidence_justification: High confidence that a specific failure root cause cannot be asserted because the only explicit result codes shown are Diameter successes (2001), and no S1-AP/GTP-C failure causes or error codes are provided in the evidence.

root_causes.issue: Metrics/aggregation inconsistency: procedure success_rate reported as 0.0 despite DIAMETER_SUCCESS evidence
root_causes.description: The PROCEDURE KPIs report success_rate 0.0 for multiple commands/procedures while simultaneously listing DIAMETER_SUCCESS as the top cause for Cmd-318/Cmd-316/Cmd-324 and the deep transactions show explicit Result-Code 2001 Answers. This indicates an inconsistency in KPI computation or sessionization in the reporting layer, not a proven network failure from packets.
root_causes.impact: May mislead operational dashboards by indicating systemic failures when the observed Diameter transactions actually succeed.
root_causes.confidence_justification: There is direct evidence of successful Diameter result codes, and direct evidence of contradictory KPI fields; however, the internal KPI logic is not observable from the capture itself, so the exact reason for the mismatch cannot be proven.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Whether any S1-AP procedure succeeded or failed (and the specific failure cause, if any)
inconclusive_aspects.reason: S1-AP entries are provided only as procedure identifiers (Proc-11/Proc-13/Proc-23) with cause=null and without the underlying initiating/success/failure messages and IEs.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Full decoded S1-AP message details including procedure direction and any Cause IEs (e.g., failure/reject messages) from the same SCTP association.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: GTP-C procedure outcome and reason (create/modify/delete and any cause codes)
inconclusive_aspects.reason: GTP-C is only evidenced as a UDP/2123 flow with 6 packets; no GTP-C message types, sequence correlation, or cause IE values are provided.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: GTP-C decoded message list (message_type, cause IE, TEID fields where applicable) for the UDP/2123 flow between 10.47.17.134 and 10.47.17.115.

inconclusive_aspects.reason: CAPTURE STATISTICS show 'GTP Tunnels: 0' and no GTP-U is listed in protocols detected; user-plane tunneling is not observable from this dataset.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on interfaces where user-plane encapsulation is visible (if applicable) or provide decoded session/tunnel records showing TEIDs/tunnel lifecycle.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Voice/IMS call setup and media quality
inconclusive_aspects.reason: No SIP, SDP, or RTP is present in protocols detected; VOICE & IMS analysis shows zero calls and no media findings.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: IMS signaling capture that includes SIP and (if assessing quality) media-plane RTP at the relevant observation point.

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Meaningful correlation between Diameter commands and a specific LTE procedure
inconclusive_aspects.reason: Diameter commands are shown only as Cmd-318/Cmd-316/Cmd-324 with success result codes; no interface/application context or correlated subscriber/session identifiers are provided beyond opaque Session-Id strings, and 'Diameter Sessions: 0' suggests incomplete sessionization.
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Diameter AVP-level decode (including Application-Id and key AVPs relevant to the command) and consistent sessionization output for the same traffic.

recommendations.action: Re-export or re-run decoding to include full S1-AP message names and Cause IEs (not just Proc-xx identifiers).
recommendations.rationale: Root cause determination for LTE control-plane issues requires explicit failure/reject messages and their cause fields; current evidence has cause=null for S1-AP procedures.

recommendations.action: Provide decoded GTP-C message types and any Cause IE values for the UDP/2123 flow (10.47.17.134 ↔ 10.47.17.115).
recommendations.rationale: GTP-C cause codes and message sequence (Create/Modify/Delete) are necessary to determine whether session control succeeded or failed; only a sparse flow summary is currently available.

recommendations.action: Investigate KPI/sessionization logic producing success_rate=0.0 while also reporting DIAMETER_SUCCESS and showing Result-Code 2001 in packets.
recommendations.rationale: Contradictory KPI outputs can trigger false alarms; packet evidence demonstrates successful Diameter Answers (2001) for multiple commands.

recommendations.action: If the goal is end-to-end service verification, capture at a known observation point and include the expected planes (control and, where applicable, user-plane).
recommendations.rationale: The capture point is UNKNOWN and 'GTP Tunnels: 0' limits conclusions about session establishment and data forwarding visibility.

session_analysis.signaling_health: Diameter signaling observed in deep transactions is successful (Result-Code 2001 for Cmd-318/Cmd-316/Cmd-324). S1-AP/X2-AP procedures are present but outcomes cannot be determined because cause and detailed message IEs are not provided.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: Not observable at this capture point: no GTP-U is listed in detected protocols and statistics show 'GTP Tunnels: 0'. DNS is present as IP-layer traffic but does not prove mobile user-plane tunnel establishment in this dataset.
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable: no SIP/SDP/RTP present in detected protocols and VOICE & IMS analysis reports zero calls and no media findings.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Limited: Diameter successes (2001) are observable, but there are no subscriber identities and no explicit linkage to S1-AP/GTP-C procedures in the provided evidence to prove an end-to-end procedure outcome.
